Really enjoyed this commission for a friend, painting her mum's garden! 😊

Happy New Year! It was an exciting but challenging year for me, with lots of good projects but very few days off. A professional highlight was finishing my first picturebook, which will be published next spring!

I was also very pleased to pass a German A2 test, travel to Stockholm, Corfu and Lisbon, do my first illustration fair, and along the way hit the gym reasonably often and build up lovely relationships with many different people.

I hope 2024 is full of peace, creativity and courage in the face of challenges, and kindness. 💚

Finished off this painting of a frosty morning at the @cubotanicgarden, showing the beautiful yoshino cherry tree and the borders around it. Final slide is the card produced from the painting, available at the @botanicgardenshop and @ccc_gallery! 😊
